[normal]Written evidence submitted by [bold]As[bold]sociation of Convenience Stores[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Recommendations:[bold]a)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Include convenience store retailers within the scope of the English carrier bag levy to encourage charitable donations.
[normal]b)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Exempt small businesses with less than 250 FTE employees from having to report back information such as the proceeds of the charge to central Government. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Support for the levy[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]Proposed small business exemption[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]“We need to charge for plastic bags. Customers will only cut back on usage if it will cost them money
[normal].
[normal] We would be delighted to give the money raised to charity
[normal],
[normal] and it would not be difficult to organise
[normal].
[normal] 
[normal]Please lobby the Government
[normal] to include small shops
[normal].” David 
[normal]Charman
[normal], Owner, 
